{
  "stem": "93.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Now, from Gotha, we went to Weimar, which, as you know, is the center of German culture and has been much described in the literature.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And it was here that we liberated Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Now, as a technicality, we did not technically liberate Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Because by the time we arrived at Buchenwald, the Germans knew that the jig was up, so to speak, and the inmates, in effect, took control of the camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "But research by our division-- historians and other people in our division-- indicate that the first American soldiers into the camp was a patrol from Company 8A of the 317th Infantry, which was my regiment.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Now, the following day I remember very, very vividly was-- that night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "That night was the night that President Roosevelt died.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And the following day, I remember very vividly Sam Williams, who commanded our Second Battalion, came to me and he said, you ought to go and look at this.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "So I went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And I went into the Buchenwald place, and here again, the horror was unspeakable.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "There were like acres of dead people, because Buchenwald was a- a true camp where they-- where they really tried to kill everybody and eliminate everybody that they could.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And the horrors were unspeakable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "I was later to find out-- although, again, I did not stay very long at Buchenwald, because we had to move eastward-- I was later find out that at Buchenwald, we had liberated things like gloves made out of the skin of men's hands.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "They-- they had taken people, cut their hands off, tanned, deboned it, and then tanned it and made these into supposedly human leather.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "There were baskets full of-- of gold teeth.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
